The United States welcomes the release of Professors Kevin King and Timothy Weeks, who were kidnapped in Afghanistan in August 2016. Both men are currently receiving medical care and support from the US Government. The US Government thanks the Afghan government for its actions and recognizes President Ashraf Ghani's efforts for peace. President Trump prioritizes the safety of American citizens and continues to work towards securing the freedom of Americans and allies held in captivity. The Trump Administration is committed to preventing Afghanistan from being used as a base for terrorist attacks against the US and its allies.